    thinking: "**Listing Necessary Skills**\n\nI\'m currently focused on the initial setup for building this full-stack e-commerce application. First, I\'m listing all available skills that might be necessary. So far I\'ve identified cloudsql-execute-sql and cloudsql-setup as potential dependencies, but I will continue reviewing other available skillsets as well.\n\n\n**Identifying Relevant Skills**\n\nI\'ve shifted my focus to identifying the most relevant skills. \"cloudsql-update-schema\" and \"firebase-integration\" might apply, but I\'m primarily focused on matching skills to the Node.js, Express, MongoDB, and JWT auth requirements. I\'m exploring \"oauth-integration\" and considering if any skills can help with mock payments or image uploads. Currently, I\'m going through the environment constraints and files in the repository to determine what\'s available.\n\n\n**Analyzing Project Setup**\n\nI\'m currently reviewing the project\'s setup and dependencies. I\'ve examined the key files like `.env.example`, `package.json`, and `vite.config.ts`. Now, I\'m identifying any skills that match the listed dependencies and environment, specifically in relation to the user\'s request for MongoDB. I\'m focusing on \"firebase-integration\" and considering how it might relate to MongoDB\'s implementation in this setup and considering the local Cloud Run limitations.\n\n\n**Considering Database Alternatives**\n\nI\'m now contemplating file-based database options for local execution, thinking a JSON-based approach with schema validation or a MongoDB API mimicry layer is the most robust solution. This avoids external dependencies and ensures compatibility with the Cloud Run sandbox. This aligns perfectly with the goal of a fully functional application.\n\nI am re-evaluating if a \"real\" MongoDB database is actually required for the user\'s need. The user specifies it should be locally runnable and extendable, so a local, robust, file-based mock database seems preferable.\n\n\n**Refining Database Implementation**\n\nI\'m now fully committed to a file-based JSON database for local execution, specifically building a robust mock database engine in `src/db/jsonDb.ts`. I believe this approach best satisfies the user\'s requirements for a locally runnable and extendable e-commerce application. I am confident it will persist data and function almost identically to a real database. I\'m verifying that we do not need Firebase or OAuth as requested by the user. I\'ve performed a quick skill check to confirm that the Gemini API is not relevant to this project.\n\n\n"
