  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Constructing Server Components**\n\nI\'ve successfully completed the authentication module at `/server/auth.ts`. My next task is to build the custom `server.ts` file in the root directory. To do that right, I need to incorporate Multer for handling image uploads. I\'ll need to configure this either directly within `/server.ts` or as a separate helper file.\n\n\n**Refining Server Structure**\n\nI\'ve decided to keep the Multer configuration directly within `/server.ts` for clarity. I\'ll also ensure the `/uploads` directory is created on server startup. The `server.ts` file will import express, path, fs, and multer. I\'ve opted for custom CORS headers middleware, which keeps everything clean and dependency-free, rather than installing the `cors` package. This aligns nicely with the server\'s core design.\n\n\n**Implementing API Endpoints**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in implementing the API endpoints within `/server.ts`. I\'ve ensured proper Vite middleware integration for development and static file serving for production. I\'ve also incorporated the necessary imports, including `path`, `fs`, and Vite\'s `createServer`. The core endpoints I\'m currently working on are registration (`POST /api/auth/register`), which will use `bcrypt.hashSync` for password hashing, and login (`POST /api/auth/login`).\n\n\n**Defining API Endpoints**\n\nI\'ve just defined the API endpoints for this project. Now, the `login` endpoint is functional; it verifies credentials using `bcrypt.compareSync` and returns a token along with user details. I\'m moving on to building out `/api/auth/me` to fetch current user details. I am also planning `/api/auth/wishlist`, which toggles a product ID, and `/api/products` endpoints with search, category, and sort parameters.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the backend Express server `/server.ts` which implements all required API endpoints for authentication, product management, order processing, custom coupon validation, administrative dashboard statistics, and image uploading via Multer. It integrates Vite as middleware in development and serves the built static files in production on port 3000."
    thinking_duration {
